snippet: A U.S. senator who says terror threats are at a high proposed a federal law Monday that carries up to five years in prison for scaling prominent national structures such as the World Trade Center, Statue of Liberty and Golden Gate Bridge....

headline.print_headline: Proposal Would Toughen Federal Trespassing Laws
headline.main: Proposal Would Toughen Federal Trespassing Laws

lead_paragraph: A U.S. senator who says terror threats are at a high proposed a federal law Monday that carries up to five years in prison for scaling prominent national structures such as the World Trade Center, Statue of Liberty and Golden Gate Bridge.
